---
description: Rebuild maxx before asking the user to run simulate/GUI or other maxx commands after code changes
alwaysApply: true
---

After editing `tools/maxxbas/` (or any file that affects the maxx binary), **do not** tell the user to run `maxx`, `maxx simulate`, or `maxx simulate --gui` until you have verified a fresh build.

**Required preflight (run it yourself, every time):**

```bash
python3 tools/ensure_maxx_built
```

- Exit code must be `0`.
- Note the printed version (e.g. `ok: maxx 0.2.40`) and include it when you tell the user to relaunch.
- If the command fails, fix the build and rerun until it passes.

`tools/maxx` also auto-rebuilds when sources are newer than the release binary, but the agent must still run `ensure_maxx_built` before suggesting the user run the sim — do not skip this step.